There is  disbursement mode called Investment loan
i)The sacco is financing you to bu land e.g they bought 20 ha, then the
loan amount should equal the value of the plot,and the member takes title deed

ii) Buy shares in stock exchange, but the sacco holds the share certificate, say for 
safaricom

GL
Sacco buys land.... debit a Land A/C or investment
					credit bank

In the sacco, they create a loan a/c called  shamba
When they disburse the land, they credit shamba with the amount of loan they
are disbursing to the memeber and debit the shamba Loan a/c



For shares, credit an account called shares loan a/c

Share charges(Withdrawal) ...always deducted from share balance--like mpesa

